{
  "texts": [
    "As the number of dendritic branches increases, the dendritic heterogeneity can provide a reasonable approximation of the synaptic heterogeneity.",
    "However, the experimental results in Supplementary b Comparison between the responses of a vanilla LIF neuron and a DH-LIF neuron to mimic the phenomenon of bursting spikes.",
    "The DH-LIF neuron enables multitimescale memories of information with different timescales.",
    "In this two-dendritic-branch example, the DH-LIF neuron presents both long-term memory of the lowfrequency inputs that regulate the bursting probability and fast response to the high-frequency inputs that drive the isolated spike events, thus generating the bursting spikes successfully while the vanilla LIF neuron fails.",
    "c Illustration of DH-SFNN constructed by DH-LIF neurons with only feedforward connections and DH-SRNN with recurrent connections."
  ]
}